bio.experienceSummary:
Hello! My name is Rachaell. 
I have 7 years of childcare experience, 4 years of eldercare experience as well as my Bachelors in Psychology. 
I'm a patient and very involved caretaker who takes pride in the positivity and peace I can bring around others. I am dependable, trustworthy and very schedule orientated. My hobbies include reading, meditation, as the occasional pizza maker!

description.displayText: Rachaell is a sweet girl very loving and caring she took care of my little boy like a big sister should.it's. Going to be hard to find someone with such patient's for my child.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hi, hope all is well!
I can definitely work the requested time frame. I have baby sat for numerous relatives and friends. The ages range from newborn to preteen. I was an after school teacher for over 12 years (elementary and middle school aged children). Simultaneously, I have been a paraprofessional for almost nine years, NYCDOE employed. I received my bachelors degree from Howard University in 2013. I have extensive training from the Office of Children and Family Services (OCFS). I have cared for six+ families and they were very pleased with me. Please feel free to inquire about anything you are unsure of. I am also currently employed by a family through care. com I have been with them for over a year. You may speak to my current employer if you should need a reference. Thank you!

description.displayText: We have used Liandra as a baby sitter once so far and will certainly do so again.  My daughter liked her very much -- she didn't want her to leave!  She was also confident and warm with my eighteen month old son (even though he has been sick and was a little more reserved than normal).  Finally, she was punctual, and good about reporting back to us how things were going.

bio.experienceSummary: Hi there! My name is Sarina and I am a recent grad from NYU Tisch working in the city as an actor and writer. I have 8 years of experience babysitting, ranging from a full-time nanny to a date night sitter! I'm a very playful and energetic sitter, and I genuinely love spending time with kids. I'm also happy to help with housework, homework, or anything you need. Many families I've worked with have commented on the joy and ease I bring to their homes. It makes me so happy to spread that!

I am 35 years-old babysitter who love to encourage children to play and learn. I am strict on homework but I also think that learning should be fun. I encourage children to sing and dance, because it help them with their education. I have been a Math tutor for more than 2 years. I also have my niece who I have help her with her homework when she need it. I am willing to help your children as much I can.

description.originalText: she is a very kind and carrying person, we all love her ❤️

bio.experienceSummary: I'm passionate about helping children grow and develop, and my five years of experience as a childcare provider have prepared me to excel in this role. I am calm, patient, and friendly, which puts children at ease, and I follow your lead when it comes to enforcing household rules and communicating about your child's day. I'm happy to care for up to four children of all ages and can help with cooking, light housekeeping, cooking or travel, and swimming supervision.

Hi! I'm Brooke and I am a 24-year-old part time ABA therapist looking for part time child care work. I moved to the city recently and prior to moving was working as a preschool teacher. I graduated from the University of Texas at Austin in May 2022 with a major in Human Development and Family Sciences and double minors in Educational Psychology and Sociology. I have been babysitting for nine years and have experience with children ages 3 months to 15 years old (I primarily work with children ages six and below). I have also worked as a camp counselor and ski instructor for children. My education and experience have given me great instincts and developmentally advantageous child care skills. 

I love animals and am comfortable with pets. I am CPR and First Aid certified. I am happy to provide references. My rate is $30 an hour for one child and increases $5/hour per child. I am available weekday mornings/early afternoon and for occasional nights depending on the day.

As the eldest of 7 children, I know it can be a huge relief for parents to have a helping hand! I started working as a mother's helper at 12 and for many years I have cared for children of all ages. My personal favorite was the one year I spent as nanny for infant twin boys, which was challenging and delightful!
I am reliable, punctual, and responsible, but also a kid at heart -- energetic, playful, and creative. When I babysit, I like to keep the kids active and engaged, i. e. reading books, playing games, spending time outdoors, doing arts and crafts, and making music! They won't be on devices all day. 
I love to cook, and I'm happy to help out with light tidying and cleaning. 
I am a professional piano teacher, so some of my afternoons and evenings are usually spent teaching lessons, however, I am flexible with scheduling! 
I am available for school drop offs and pickups, date nights, and play dates!

Hi! My name is Jen and I am 28 years old living in Downtown Jersey City. I graduated college in 2015 with a degree in Early Childhood Education and with a minor in reading. I currently have 3 years of experience being a full time teacher under my belt. I have taught both 1st and 3rd grade, along with having numerous field/student teaching experiences ranging with children from ages 2-10 years old. Although I am no longer in the education field and have transitioned into sales for healthcare- I still have such a strong love for children due to my first profession and years of study. I would love to be a caregiver to yours during the time you need me!

description.displayText: Jennifer has experience as a teacher of young children and it shows. She is so great with kids and has the added benefit of being a great tutor! Always on time and very organized and dependable. Cannot recommend highly enough.
description.originalText: Jennifer has experience as a teacher of young children and it shows. She is so great with kids and has the added benefit of being a great tutor! Always on time and very organized and dependable. Cannot recommend highly enough.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello! I am a Brooklyn-based writer seeking part-time sitting work! I graduated from Kenyon College in 2020, where I studied political science and French. I have experience working with a range of ages, from 17 months - 13 years, and have been working with multiple families in Brooklyn since moving to New York last year. I am enthusiastic, energetic, organized, and adore working with kids! I also have experience in theatre and the arts, and love doing hands-on projects. 

I'm also available to help out with schoolwork. I spent three years helping third-grade students learn how to read with "Start Making A Reader Today" and volunteered as a lunch buddy to elementary school kids while I was in college. My academic writing has been published by the Yale Review of International Studies and the Brookings Institution, and I've worked on Capitol Hill, as a fact-checker, and as a podcast producer.

I work part-time in a highly regarded preschool where I care for children from infancy through elementary age. 
I love it because we use the latest research in child development to create the curriculum. And that research drives how we work with, care for and teach children. 
In my off time, I like working as an occasional babysitter for different families who need me.

I went to school for design and I never met an art project or craft project I didn't love. Legos anyone? 

My son, who has learning differences, gave me insight into how children's brains work. That experience has been incredibly helpful when caring for other children. Because what works for him seems to work for all kids. 
A gentle touch, extra patience and being tuned into a child's needs. Needs sometimes spoken and sometimes unspoken. 
I have references, been fingerprinted, background checked and am CPR certified. Experience with kids with mild Autism, ADHD and dylsexia

description.originalText:
Charlie was everything I could have hoped for and more when looking for someone to look after my 11 month old son. She has such a calming and reassuring presence and I felt completely at ease while my son was in her care. 
She is a complete professional and was amenable to my sons schedule.
I will be calling Charlie again in a heartbeat when we need help again. 
Thank you Charlie!!
